post_text: ATTENTION: The Houston Independent School District is relaunching curbside student meals distribution on Tuesday, Sept. 8. HISD Nutrition Services will offer daily pickup, Monday through Friday from 10 a.m. to 1 p.m. at 86 schools. Each day, families can go to any location to pick up one pre-packed breakfast and lunch meal per student at no cost. Parents must show proof of enrollment in an HISD school — such as a student ID or report card — to pick up the meals. For more information on student meals offered during virtual learning and a complete list of curbside pickup locations and times, visit HoustonISD.org/StudentMeals.

HAPPENING TODAY: #HISD, Houston Food Bank distributing food for families and student meals from 2 to 7 p.m. TODAY at NRG Stadium.

Each family will receive up to 60 pounds of food and a weeks’ worth of student breakfast and lunch meals. Community food packages are available to all.

For student meals, the driver must have children in the car or show proof of enrollment in any school district (report card, student id, etc.) or birth certificate. To participate, enter through yellow lot main entrance off South Main. More info: www.HoustonISD.org/Nutrition

Mark your calendars: #HISD Nutrition Services and the Houston Food Bank will be distributing student meals and food for families on Friday (8/14) from 2 to 7 p.m. at NRG Park. Each family will receive up to 60 pounds of food and a weeks’ worth of student breakfast and lunch meals. Community food packages are available to all.

For student meals, the driver must have children in the car or show proof of enrollment in any school district (report card, student id, etc.) or birth certificate. To participate, enter through yellow lot main entrance off South Main. More info: www.HoustonISD.org/Nutrition

post_text: Join Kinder HSPVA today at 4 pm on Facebook for their first HSPVA Visual Arts Virtual Senior Show. Celebrate the hard work of these amazing students!
shared_text:
Looking Glass - A Kinder HSPVA Visual Arts Virtual Senior Show

Kinder HSPVA premiered a video.
April 26 at 8:49 AM ·

Join us for the opening of our first Virtual Senior Show from our Visual Arts department featuring the work of Leah Clemons, Gabrielle Lansangan, and Evelyn Wattenbarger. Prepare your favorite drinks and enjoy your favorite at home hors d'oeuvres.
One of the highlights for seniors at Kinder HSPVA is a culminating performance or art show celebrating the four years of work that every student has created. Because of the transition to virtual learning, many of our seniors did not have that experience.
For our Visual Arts students who did not get to have a physical Senior Show, some have created a virtual show that will be able to celebrate their work with friends, family and the community.
“Looking Glass” celebrates the work of three seniors and represents how all of us interpret lives through our own eyes and our own art.
• Leah Clemons – will pursue a major in Fiber at Kansas City Art Institute next year
• Gabrielle Lansangan – will study Biology at University of Houston
• Evelyn Wattenbarger – will study Biomedical Mechanical Engineering at University of Ottawa next year

post_text: As a result of a major water main break in East Houston that has impacted multiple areas of the city, #HISD after-school activities are cancelled today (2/27). All playoff games will be held as scheduled. Campus dismissals will be held as normal. If needed, bus drivers will use alternate routes. HISD maintenance staff will also inspect buildings as a precautionary measure to ensure all systems are functioning properly once water is restored.

The morning is off to a great start in HISD at Eliot ES as Interim Superintendent Lathan surprised Principal Zandra Aguilar as the district’s Elementary Principal of the Year for the 2019-2020 school year!

Principal Aguilar is not only being recognized for leading one of the district’s A-rated campuses, but for her tenured leadership in building teachers’ capacity and fostering relationships with students and the community!

Congratulations again to Principal Zandra Aguilar at Eliot ES for being the district’s 2019-2020 Elementary Principal of the Year.

Yesterday, HISD Interim Superintendent Dr. Grenita Lathan met privately with a group of Bellaire HS students to discuss their safety concerns, and to let students know that their voices are heard and that the district shares their concerns.

Afterward, it was announced that the district will explore the following safety & security steps:
- Metal Detectors
- Safety & Security Council Committees
- Meeting with student representatives
- Key Community Leaders Safety Meeting
- Community Input on safety recommendations

READ more about the visit here: http://bit.ly/30PCXgt

REMINDER: If you SEE something, SAY something. If you would like to give an anonymous tip, please call our anonymous tip line at 713-641-7446 or visit http://bit.ly/2EPGMb1.

post_text:
We are excited to announce that Jack Yates High School has received official authorization to operate as International Baccalaureate World School! It will be one of five HISD high schools authorized to offer the IB Diploma.

Starting next year, 11th graders will have the opportunity to participate in the program, which empowers students to become bilingual and bi-literate learners who embrace multiculturalism and diversity. Read more at https://bit.ly/30aXrQn
